4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING ALCOHOL LAWS TO PROVIDE THAT A LICENSEE
5 MAY COMPENSATE A CONCESSIONAIRE BASED ON A PERCENTAGE OF GROSS OR NET ALCOHOLIC
6 BEVERAGE SALES; AND AMENDING SECTION 16-4-418, MCA.”
7
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
9
10 Section 1. Section 16-4-418, MCA, is amended to read:
11 "16-4-418. Concession agreements. (1) Except for entities licensed under 16-4-105(1)(e) or 16-4-
12 201(8) on or after January 1, 2021, the department may allow entities licensed under 16-4-105 or 16-4-201 to
13 enter into concession agreements with unlicensed entities to serve alcoholic beverages. A licensee may enter
14 into a maximum of three concession agreements for each license at any given time.
15 (2) To be considered for approval, a concession agreement must:
16 (a) demonstrate that the licensed premises is a contiguous premises that includes the space
17 utilized by the concessionaire; and
18 (b) provide that the licensee retains ultimate control over and responsibility for operating the
19 license, including:
20 (i) the ordering, purchase, sale, and service of alcoholic beverages;
21 (ii) the right to discipline or otherwise sanction any employee in relation to the service of alcoholic
22 beverages;
23 (iii) reconciling the proceeds of alcoholic beverage sales at least monthly;
24 (iv) terminating the concession agreement with cause where cause includes but is not limited to
25 any violation of Title 16 and the sale or transfer of the license; and
26 (v) the exclusive operation of all gaming activities if the licensee offers any gaming.
27 (3) A licensee's gaming endorsement may not be extended through a concession agreement.
28 (4) Nothing in this section precludes a licensee and a concessionaire from sharing employees.
