2 of the premises that must be a continuous area under the control of the licensee or the concessionaire and not
3 interrupted by any area in which one of the parties does not have control.
4 (b) The term includes multiple floors on the premises and common areas necessarily shared by
5 multiple building tenants in order to allow patrons to access other tenant businesses or private dwellings in the
6 same building, including but not limited to entryways, hallways, stairwells, and elevators."
